ervices.\r\n\r\n\r\nSQL & Libraries\r\n\r\nWorked with SQL procedures, views, wrote complex sql queries including aggregate functions, sub queries, nested queries and joins.\r\nDesigned and optimized PostgreSQL database schemas, reducing query response times.\r\nAssisted in restructuring database architecture and data retrieval using PHP and MySQL, reducing databaseretrieval times.\r\nDesigned and implemented robust, high-traffic MySQL database architecture, and integrated Redis as an in-memory data structure store for efficient caching, enhancing data processing speeds by 40%.\r\nUsing complex SQL to create detailed reports to the specifications of the production teams.\r\nImproved site speed by optimizing database queries and server configurations resulting in a 25%improvement in load times.\r\nImproved database performance by optimizing queries and indexing resulting in a 20% reduction in querytime.\r\nCrafted intricate stored procedures and user-defined functions meeting business requirements forcustom reports.\r\n\r\nProduction Support\r\n\r\nResponsible for maintenance and debugging of existing applications(production support), fixing bugs, and improving functionality. Optimized database performance and implemented caching mechanisms to improve application performance and speed, ensuring smooth operation and customer satisfaction.\r\nHad an active part in resolving an average of 10 technical issues per week, resulting in a 25% increase in overall system efficiency.\r\nMonitored performance of applications to identify issues or bottlenecks in order to improve theirefficiency. 3x performance increase.\r\nResponsibility for the entire technical infrastructure of the company ensuring 99.9% uptime.\r\n\r\n\r\nTest Cases\r\n\r\nWrote unit test and functional test using PHPUnit and Symfony WebTestCase component.\r\nImplemented automated testing frameworks for web applications to ensure quality control standardswere met.\r\n', 1, '2024-01-25 12:03:44', '2024-01-25 12: