gth. The net income after taxes and realized investment gains was $698 million, reflecting the company\'s ability to navigate through difficult times.\r\nIn addition to its financial performance, Mutual of Omaha\'s commitment to its policyholders is evident. The company\'s focus on providing outstanding service to its customers is reflected in its ability to provide COVID-related benefit payments to thousands of customers and their beneficiaries. This commitment, along with the dedication and contributions of the company\'s associates, has enabled Mutual of Omaha to overcome challenges and deliver for its policyholders.\r\nAs a highly rated, Fortune 500 organization, Mutual of Omaha offers a variety of insurance and financial products for individuals, businesses, and groups throughout the United States. Being a mutual company owned by its policyholders, Mutual of Omaha is well-positioned for the future and committed to providing exceptional service to its customers.\r\n\r\n3E Company\r\nAbout the Company:\r\n3E Company is a global provider of intelligent compliance solutions, focusing on Environmental Health and Safety (EHS) and product compliance expertise. With over 30 years of experience, they have earned the trust of leading companies worldwide. Their solutions empower clients to improve chemical and workplace safety, product safety, and supply chain transparency. 3E company is deeply committed to serving over 5,000 customers worldwide, including major chemical manufacturers, retailers, and pharmaceutical companies. They are dedicated to building a safer world and a more sustainable future through actionable intelligence and ESG performance improvement.\r\n3E Company\'s dedication to ensuring safety and sustainability, one product, one workplace, and one community at a time, has made it a trusted partner for organizations seeking to meet regulatory obligations while capturing market opportunities. Their expertise in EHS&S and product compliance enables clients t