e challenges and deliver for its policyholders.\r\nAs a highly rated, Fortune 500 organization, Mutual of Omaha offers a variety of insurance and financial products for individuals, businesses, and groups throughout the United States. Being a mutual company owned by its policyholders, Mutual of Omaha is well-positioned for the future and committed to providing exceptional service to its customers.\r\n\r\n3E Company\r\nAbout the Company:\r\n3E Company is a global provider of intelligent compliance solutions, focusing on Environmental Health and Safety (EHS) and product compliance expertise. With over 30 years of experience, they have earned the trust of leading companies worldwide. Their solutions empower clients to improve chemical and workplace safety, product safety, and supply chain transparency. 3E company is deeply committed to serving over 5,000 customers worldwide, including major chemical manufacturers, retailers, and pharmaceutical companies. They are dedicated to building a safer world and a more sustainable future through actionable intelligence and ESG performance improvement.\r\n3E Company\'s dedication to ensuring safety and sustainability, one product, one workplace, and one community at a time, has made it a trusted partner for organizations seeking to meet regulatory obligations while capturing market opportunities. Their expertise in EHS&S and product compliance enables clients to accelerate the development and launch of products designed with safety from the start, ultimately contributing to a safer world and a more sustainable future.\r\nCompany Business and Targeted Audience/Mission:\r\n3E Company is a leading company based in Canton, Ohio. It is known for its expertise in environmental health and safety compliance and information management. The company provides a comprehensive suite of data and information services to help organizations comply with stringent regulatory requirements and ensure workplace safety. 3E Company\'s solutions include regulatory content, 24/7 emergency response services, regulatory reporting, and workplace safety training. The company\'s commitment to excellence and innovation has made it a trusted partner for businesses across various industries.\r\nREVENUE MODEL:\r\n3E Company is a leading provider of environmental health and safety (EHS) compliance and information management services. The company offers a range of solutions to help businesses comply with regulations, manage risk, and improve workplace safety. 3E Company\'s revenue model is based on subscription services, consulting fees, and software licensing. The company provides its clients with access to a comprehensive database of regulatory content, as well as software tools for managing compliance and reporting. Additionally, 3E Company offers consulting services to help businesses develop and implement effective EHS management strategies. The company\'s revenue is generated through annual subscription fees for access to its regulatory content and software, as well as fees for consulting services and software licensing. This diversified revenue model allows 3E Company to provide value-added services to its clients while maintaining a steady stream of income.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n3E\'s estimated annual revenue is currently $222.3M per year.\r\n3E\'s estimated revenue per employee is $294,000\r\n3E has 756 Employees.\r\n3E grew its employee count by 25% last year.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChegg\r\nAbout Chegg:\r\nChegg is an education technology company that offers a variety of services and products to support students in their academic journey. Here are key points about Chegg:\r\nProducts Under Chegg:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTextbook Solutions: Chegg provides a vast database of step-by-step textbook solutions for a wide range of academic subjects, aiding students in understanding complex concepts.\r\nStudy Resources: Chegg offers study resources such as practice problems, flashcards, and study guides to help students reinforce their learn